    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Material having the formula Co3(AsO4)2, used as a colorant in paints, glass, glazes, and enamels. It occurs in nature as cobalt bloom or erythrite; it was synthetically produced in 1880. It is highly toxic by ingestion, inhalation, and skin contact.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
